I"<p>Here are few tips to ensure a good night’s sleep</p>

<p>– Have a schedule for the day</p>

<p>– Make room for at least 6-8 hours of sleep</p>

<p>– The body produces sleep hormone melatonin only in the dark. So create a dark environment in the bedroom</p>

<p>– Drink a cup of milk before going to sleep</p>

<p>– use an eye band</p>

<p>– Practice relaxation techniques such as yoga, meditation</p>

<p>– Wash face in lukewarm water before sleeping</p>

<p>– Cultivate bedtime reading habits</p>
